# Project Aura - Root Build-Context Ignore Rules
#
# All Dockerfiles under ``deploy/docker/`` build with the repo root as
# context (`docker build -f <subdir>/Dockerfile.X .`). Without this
# file, ``COPY .`` or wildcards risk pulling secrets, local state, and
# build artifacts into the image layer (even if they're never
# referenced, they're tarred up and shipped to the daemon and can leak
# via image inspection or shared layer caches).
#
# Per the 2026-05-14 ultrareview (Tara's container-policy pass): verify
# no .env, .aws/, or *.pem can land in any Docker build context. The
# .dockerignore in deploy/docker/test-harness/ is a duplicate set of
# rules for anyone who builds from that subdir directly.

# Credentials / secrets
.env
.env.*
.aws/
.kube/
.ssh/
*.pem
*.key
*.cer
*.p12
credentials
credentials.json
service-account.json
.npmrc

# Local Python / Node state
.venv/
venv/
__pycache__/
*.pyc
*.pyo
.pytest_cache/
.mypy_cache/
.ruff_cache/
.coverage
htmlcov/
node_modules/

# OS / IDE
.DS_Store
.idea/
.vscode/
*.swp
*.swo

# Build artifacts
build/
dist/
*.egg-info/

# Worktrees / agent state (large + irrelevant to every image)
.claude/worktrees/

# Git history (ship the working tree, not the full history;
# Dockerfiles that actually need git history use a build arg).
.git/
.gitignore

# Frontend dev artifacts
frontend/build/
frontend/dist/
frontend/.vite/
